snippet.textDisplay: I think there was a part of Harry that wanted to leave the Royal life before he even met Meghan. Having said that, yes, Meghan probably gave him the courage and support he needed to do that. She was not raised for the type of life she was thrown into by marrying a royal. I'm sure his other girlfriends were molded for that type of life from early childhood. It's not a surprise that Harry would try a life he's only fantasized about now that he has a wife that supports the idea and a family of his own. But I do hope they will return after a year. I just hope that if they do return that the queen has more foresight, more understanding of what Harry and Meghan feel they need to be able to have a more balanced and healthy life and still perform their duties as part of the royal family. I respect Harry for trying to do what he feels is best for his wife and I respect Meghan for doing her best to adjust to such a foreign lifestyle.  I hope that in a year they can all find a happy medium and come together. I wish them the best.

Up until the queen took Diana's HRH away, I was a true Royalist, in the days when the National Anthem was played at the end of the days transmission on the TV I would always stand until it went off, so this attitude I have now is down to the queens own behavior.
